<br>
South west of the druid ring is a large area called the ancient combine outpost.  Generally, it is quite safe here (I have never had a problem) so you realy don't have to worry about adds.  You are looking for a pyramid that is hollow towards the northern side of the outpost.  Inside you will see a series of plaguebones 'marching' inside.  It is pretty easy to single pull if your timing is right.  Here is what I do...<br>
<br>
Casala, 41 mage, focus water pet with summoned plate, dagger of symbols, etc...  BOII, Barrier of Combustion and park him outside the entrance.  I'll use my clay bracelet (clicky eye of zomm) to go in and watch for a single plaguebone going in front of the entrance.  As soon as I see a single plaguebone walking in front, i'll use my white ceramic band (right click burst of flame) to pull then have pet engage outside the pyramid.<br>
<br>
Generally, you will find that once the plaguebone gets down in health you can simply nuke it about twice with blaze.  i've never had blaze resisted and it does nearly full damage each time.  for whatever reason, however, i've had cinder bolt resisted a number of times /ponder.  when you get done with the fight your pet will be at low health.  which is no problem.  have your water pet sit down and watch in amazement as he heals up quick.  rinse, repeat.  most mobs drop anywhere between 2 gp and 5 pp and exp is about 1-2% depending on level (i.e. up to half a blue).  all of this in a very safe location...not too bad.<br>
<br>
plaguebone thief - lvl 36-38<br>
- great ones to pull.  they don't often hit your armored pet.<br>
<br>
plaguebone skeleton - lvl 33 - 37<br>
- also great to pull.  they are easy to kill.<br>
<br>
greater plaguebone - lvl 40-43<br>
- these take a little more work.  might have to chain cast pets for this one.  might want to hold off nuking until after the second pet.<br>
<br>
one other little note of interest.  if you find yourself having to chain cast...make sure you have SoW potions.  in that unlikely even you fizzle, get interrupted, or otherwise can't summon a pet, you can easily run away with SoW and then summon another pet...head back to the pyramid and re-engage.<br>
<br>
hope this helps...<br>
<br>
